                <h1>Understanding Grutter v. Bollinger: A Landmark Affirmative Action Case</h1>
                <p>Grutter v. Bollinger (2003) is a landmark Supreme Court case that upheld the affirmative action policy at the University of Michigan Law School. The court ruled that considering race as one of many factors in admissions is constitutional. This decision reinforced the importance of diversity in higher education.</p>
